{
  "video_id": "hXiGaV8tY5M",
  "title": "Discovering Truth",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 540.0,
      "end_time": 4230.0,
      "text": "Well over 100 years ago, an American poet"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 4230.0,
      "end_time": 7470.0,
      "text": "put to rhyme an ancient parable."
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 7470.0,
      "end_time": 10530.0,
      "text": "The first verse of the poem speaks about:"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 10530.0,
      "end_time": 12540.0,
      "text": "\"Six men of Indostan"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 12540.0,
      "end_time": 15329.0,
      "text": "To learning much inclined,"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 15330.0,
      "end_time": 17930.0,
      "text": "Who went to see the Elephant"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 17930.0,
      "end_time": 20370.0,
      "text": "(Though all of them were blind),"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 20370.0,
      "end_time": 23310.0,
      "text": "That each by observation"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 23310.0,
      "end_time": 26490.0,
      "text": "Might satisfy his mind.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 26490.0,
      "end_time": 29459.0,
      "text": "In the poem, each of the six travelers"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 29460.0,
      "end_time": 31830.0,
      "text": "takes hold of a different part of the elephant"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 31830.0,
      "end_time": 36000.0,
      "text": "and then describes to the others what he has discovered."
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 36000.0,
      "end_time": 38850.0,
      "text": "One of the men finds the elephant&#39;s leg"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 38850.0,
      "end_time": 43950.0,
      "text": "and describes it as being round and rough like a tree."
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 43950.0,
      "end_time": 46350.0,
      "text": "Another feels the tusk and describes the elephant"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 46350.0,
      "end_time": 47940.0,
      "text": "as a spear."
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 47940.0,
      "end_time": 52589.0,
      "text": "A third grabs the tail and insists that an elephant"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 52590.0,
      "end_time": 54620.0,
      "text": "is like a rope."
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 54620.0,
      "end_time": 58410.0,
      "text": "A fourth discovers the trunk and insists that the elephant"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 58410.0,
      "end_time": 61500.0,
      "text": "is like a large snake."
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 61500.0,
      "end_time": 64690.0,
      "text": "Each is describing truth."
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 64690.0,
      "end_time": 68910.0,
      "text": "And because his truth comes from personal experience,"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 68910.0,
      "end_time": 73979.0,
      "text": "each insists that he knows what he knows."
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 73980.0,
      "end_time": 75930.0,
      "text": "The poem concludes:"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 75930.0,
      "end_time": 78300.0,
      "text": "\"And so these men of Indostan"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 78300.0,
      "end_time": 80399.0,
      "text": "Disputed loud and long,"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 80400.0,
      "end_time": 83490.0,
      "text": "Each in his own opinion"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 83490.0,
      "end_time": 85770.0,
      "text": "Exceeding stiff and strong,"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 85770.0,
      "end_time": 88920.0,
      "text": "Though each was partly in the right,"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 88920.0,
      "end_time": 92470.0,
      "text": "And all were in the wrong!\""
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 92470.0,
      "end_time": 94440.0,
      "text": "That someone could make a judgment"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 94440.0,
      "end_time": 98429.0,
      "text": "based on one aspect of truth and apply it"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 98430.0,
      "end_time": 104700.0,
      "text": "to the whole seems absurd or even unbelievable."
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 104700.0,
      "end_time": 108270.0,
      "text": "On the other hand, have we ever been guilty of the same pattern"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 108270.0,
      "end_time": 110100.0,
      "text": "of thought?"
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 110100.0,
      "end_time": 112800.0,
      "text": "We have so many examples of things"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 112800.0,
      "end_time": 117970.0,
      "text": "that mankind once knew were true but have since proven false."
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 117970.0,
      "end_time": 122390.0,
      "text": "For example, in spite of one-time overwhelming"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 122400.0,
      "end_time": 124490.0,
      "text": "consensus, the earth isn&#39;t flat."
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 124490.0,
      "end_time": 128700.0,
      "text": "The stars don&#39;t revolve around the earth."
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 128699.99999999999,
      "end_time": 133281.0,
      "text": "And of course, man actually can fly, even break"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 133281.0,
      "end_time": 134300.0,
      "text": "the sound barrier."
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 139510.0,
      "end_time": 141640.0,
      "text": "Often truth is rejected because it"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 141640.0,
      "end_time": 145720.0,
      "text": "doesn&#39;t appear to be consistent with previous experiences."
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 150250.0,
      "end_time": 155500.0,
      "text": "The thing about truth is that it exists beyond belief."
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 159750.0,
      "end_time": 166530.0,
      "text": "It is true even if nobody believes it."
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 166530.0,
      "end_time": 168960.0,
      "text": "We simply don&#39;t know all things."
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 168960.0,
      "end_time": 171600.0,
      "text": "We can&#39;t see everything."
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 171600.0,
      "end_time": 175140.0,
      "text": "Because we see through a glass darkly,"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 175140.0,
      "end_time": 180869.0,
      "text": "we have to trust the Lord, who sees all things clearly."
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 180870.0,
      "end_time": 184800.0,
      "text": "That is because there is one source of truth"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 184800.0,
      "end_time": 188620.0,
      "text": "that is complete, correct, and incorruptible."
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 188620.0,
      "end_time": 192430.0,
      "text": "That source is our infinitely wise and all-knowing Heavenly"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 192430.0,
      "end_time": 193740.0,
      "text": "Father."
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 193740.0,
      "end_time": 199380.0,
      "text": "He knows truth as it was, as it is, and as it yet will be."
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 199380.0,
      "end_time": 202560.0,
      "text": "Our loving Heavenly Father offers His truth"
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 202560.0,
      "end_time": 205470.0,
      "text": "to us, His mortal children."
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 205470.0,
      "end_time": 208200.0,
      "text": "Now, what is this truth?"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 208200.0,
      "end_time": 211260.0,
      "text": "It is the gospel of Jesus Christ."
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 211260.0,
      "end_time": 216989.0,
      "text": "Jesus Christ--He is \"the way, the truth, and the life.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 216990.0,
      "end_time": 222570.0,
      "text": "As you accept the responsibility to seek after truth"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 222570.0,
      "end_time": 225450.0,
      "text": "with an open mind and a humble heart,"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 225450.0,
      "end_time": 228149.0,
      "text": "you will become more tolerant of others,"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 228150.0,
      "end_time": 231870.0,
      "text": "more open to listen, more prepared to understand,"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 231870.0,
      "end_time": 237600.0,
      "text": "more inclined to build up instead of tearing down."
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 237600.0,
      "end_time": 243930.0,
      "text": "And you will be more willing to go where God wants you to go."
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 243930.0,
      "end_time": 246540.0,
      "text": "It is my prayer that you will seek"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 246540.0,
      "end_time": 250490.0,
      "text": "the truth earnestly and unceasingly,"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 250500.0,
      "end_time": 254880.0,
      "text": "that you will yearn to drink from the fount of all truth,"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 254880.0,
      "end_time": 259529.0,
      "text": "whose waters are pure and sweet, \"a well of water"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 259529.0,
      "end_time": 263690.0,
      "text": "springing up into everlasting life.\""
    }
  ]
}